  "body": "### Description\n\nCurrently, the Quarkus Kubernetes extension allows mounting volumes for secrets as directories. However, it would also be good to allow the mounting of single files from the secrets. Example:\r\n\r\nIf we want to mount the following:\r\n```\r\napiVersion: apps/v1\r\nkind: Deployment\r\nmetadata:\r\n  name: my-app\r\nspec:\r\n  template:\r\n    spec:\r\n      containers:\r\n        - volumeMounts:\r\n            - mountPath: /etc/certs\r\n              name: volume-certs\r\n      volumes:\r\n        - name: volume-certs\r\n          secret:\r\n            secretName: rootsecretname\r\n            items:\r\n              - key: keystore.p12\r\n                path: keystore.p12\r\n```\r\n\r\nTo achieve the above deployment, we can't use the existing properties in https://quarkus.io/guides/deploying-to-kubernetes#secret-volumes as it only works for folders.\r\n\r\nTherefore, it would be a nice to have to allow having something like:\r\n\r\n```\r\nquarkus.kubernetes.mounts.volume-certs.path=/etc/certs\r\nquarkus.kubernetes.secret-volumes.volume-certs.secret-name=root-secret\r\nquarkus.kubernetes.secret-volumes.volume-certs.items.keystore.path=keystore.p12\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Note**: The only new change here would be the new **items** property under **volume-certs**.\r\nAnd hence the Quarkus Kubernetes would generate the above Deployment manifest. \r\n\r\n__Perhaps, this might imply changes in Dekorate as well__\n\n### Implementation ideas\n\n_No response_",
